[b]Wyckoff Schematics[/b] automatically identifies Wyckoff accumulation and distribution phases in real time and labels the key structural events that define each phase.

[b]What it does[/b]

Wyckoff analysis is typically done manually by identifying specific event sequences — a Selling Climax, a Spring, a Sign of Strength, and so on. This indicator attempts to automate that identification: detecting the current phase, tracking its sub-phases, and labeling each event as it forms. A real-time dashboard summarizes the current phase state and Composite Operator tracking.

[b]Phases and events detected[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Accumulation[/b] — Selling Climax (SC), Automatic Rally (AR), Secondary Test (ST), Spring, Sign of Strength (SOS)
[*][b]Distribution[/b] — Buying Climax (BC), Automatic Reaction (AR), Secondary Test (ST), Upthrust After Distribution (UTAD), Sign of Weakness (SOW)
[*][b]Phase transitions[/b] — Colored boxes mark phase ranges; alerts fire on transitions
[/list]

[b]Analytical framework[/b]

[list]
[*]Wyckoff's 2nd Law (Cause and Effect) — measuring the cause built in a range against the effect of the subsequent move
[*]Wyckoff's 3rd Law (Effort vs. Result) — detecting divergences between volume effort and price result
[*]Composite Operator tracking — identifying probable accumulation or distribution by large interests
[/list]

[b]Alerts[/b]
All alerts fire only on confirmed bar close by default (configurable via "Alerts only on bar close" toggle).
[list]
[*][b]Accumulation Started[/b] — accumulation phase detected
[*][b]Distribution Started[/b] — distribution phase detected
[*][b]Markup Started[/b] — markup (uptrend) phase beginning
[*][b]Markdown Started[/b] — markdown (downtrend) phase beginning
[*][b]Spring Detected[/b] — spring event identified in accumulation
[*][b]UTAD Detected[/b] — upthrust after distribution event identified
[*][b]Test Detected[/b] — test event detected within a phase
[*][b]SOS Detected[/b] — sign of strength confirmed
[*][b]SOW Detected[/b] — sign of weakness confirmed
[*][b]SOSB Breakout[/b] — SOS breakout above range resistance
[*][b]SOWB Breakdown[/b] — SOW breakdown below range support
[*][b]LPS Detected[/b] — last point of support identified
[*][b]LPSY Detected[/b] — last point of supply identified
[*][b]Climax Detected[/b] — buying or selling climax detected
[*][b]Spring + Test Confirmed[/b] — spring followed by successful test
[*][b]UTAD + Test Confirmed[/b] — UTAD followed by successful test
[*][b]High Quality Accumulation Setup[/b] — high-scoring accumulation structure
[*][b]High Quality Distribution Setup[/b] — high-scoring distribution structure
[*][b]HTF/LTF Aligned[/b] — higher and lower timeframe phases align
[/list]

